\begin_inset Formula $\emptyset$
\end_inset

 which means the total probability may be excessed than one. In particular, 
\begin_inset Formula $\likely\vee\likely=\overflow$
\end_inset

 because the probability of two disjoint events should not both bigger than 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

